AGI - A new internal confrontation is testing the Israeli government led by Benjamin Netanyahu. Defense Minister Yoav Gallant expressed himself with very explicit words against the hypothesis of military and civil control of the Strip at the end of the war. "I repeat clearly: I will not accept the establishment of an Israeli military administration in Gaza, Israel must not have civil control over Gaza," said Gallant in a press conference, according to the Israeli press. "I ask Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu to declare that Israel will not establish civil control or military leadership in the Gaza Strip."
&nbsp;
According to the minister, challenged by the far-right colleagues of the government and the same prime minister, it is necessary that the Palestinians indicate an alternative authority to Hamas to lead the Strip. "The first condition to prepare the ground for another entity is to destroy Hamas and do so without an apology," Netanyahu reacted on Telegram. After the terrible massacre of October 7, I ordered the destruction of Hamas," said Netanyahu responding to Gallant. "As long as Hamas remains intact, no other party will be able to intervene to manage civil affairs in Gaza, certainly not the Palestinian Authority. 80% of Palestinians in Judea and Samaria support the terrible massacre of 7 October," Netanyahu said, referring to the West Bank with its biblical names.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
To ask for the dismissal of Gallant intervened the Minister of National Security and "falco" of the executive, Itamar Ben Gvir. "The Defence Minister who failed on October 7 and who continues to fail today must be replaced to achieve the objectives of the war". "The Israeli people will not accept to deliver Gaza to the control of the Palestinian terrorist authority" and its security "will be guaranteed only by determination to win", said the Justice Minister, Yariv Levin, a member of the Likud as Netanyahu. Gallant "has announced today its support for the creation of a Palestinian terrorist state", attacked Betzalel Smotrich, Minister of Finance of the extreme right. "An alternative government to Hamas will be prepared immediately," he added.&nbsp;
